I've been eating a bit too much lately.

37
00:02:00,319 --> 00:02:01,439
You've got to catch me.

38
00:02:01,439 --> 00:02:03,079
Don't worry. I can catch you.

39
00:02:03,079 --> 00:02:05,680
Come on. Give me your hand.

40
00:02:06,439 --> 00:02:08,456
Come on.

41
00:02:21,888 --> 00:02:23,560
I'm sorry.

42
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:26,120
I'm too fat for you to catch.

43
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:31,208
It's okay.

44
00:02:35,479 --> 00:02:37,840
Ling Weiyi, you have to say yes.

45
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:39,080
We won the game,

46
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:41,280
it's all thanks to Qi Yu.

47
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:42,720
How can you use a beauty trap like this?

48
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:43,759
It's okay, Weiyi.

49
00:02:43,759 --> 00:02:46,439
If you don't say yes, next year
we'll have Qi Yu support our department.

50
00:02:46,439 --> 00:02:48,199
We'll beat you all.

51
00:02:48,199 --> 00:02:50,599
What does it matter to me
whether you win the game or not?

52
00:02:50,599 --> 00:02:52,599
Anyway, I support the team
whichever team Qi Yu is in.

53
00:02:52,599 --> 00:02:54,728
After all, he will win.

54
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:00,520
Does it count as a yes?

55
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:02,664
Wait.

56
00:03:03,759 --> 00:03:06,000
Do you really like me?

57
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:11,479
So, will you treat me the best?

58
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:13,640
Of course.

59
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:22,216
Alright then.

60
00:03:56,599 --> 00:03:58,639
Do you still like me?

61
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:07,479
You can just say it.

62
00:04:07,479 --> 00:04:10,240
Hesitating is not your style.

63
00:04:14,039 --> 00:04:19,040
Sorry, actually I've wanted
to call and apologize to you every day.

64
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:24,040
But I don't think it's going to work this time.

65
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,000
You don't need to apologize to me.

66
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,839
You haven't done anything wrong.

67
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:46,560
There are some problems between us.

68
00:04:47,720 --> 00:04:49,279
Actually, we don't have to

69
00:04:49,279 --> 00:04:52,839
solve these problems, right?

70
00:04:54,759 --> 00:04:58,079
I like you, and you like me.

71
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:01,240
Then why do we have to consider

72
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:05,639
the money, house and all that stuff?

73
00:05:05,639 --> 00:05:08,959
Can't we just love each other day by day?

74
00:05:09,399 --> 00:05:12,279
That way, I don't have to change myself,

75
00:05:12,279 --> 00:05:14,519
and you don't need to make yourself

76
00:05:14,519 --> 00:05:18,800
under great pressure, right?

77
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:24,279
Weiyi, I know you don't want to accept it.

78
00:05:24,279 --> 00:05:26,344
Neither do I.

79
00:05:27,639 --> 00:05:30,040
But I have to think about our future.

80
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:32,439
But you never know the future.

81
00:05:32,439 --> 00:05:35,360
Can't we just live happily day by day?

82
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:37,680
We had agreed

83
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:40,240
to watch the sunrise and sunset together,

84
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:43,560
stay home and watch movies when it rains,

85
00:05:44,199 --> 00:05:46,519
go out for a picnic when it's sunny,

86
00:05:46,519 --> 00:05:50,279
go surfing in summer and skiing in winter.

87
00:05:50,519 --> 00:05:53,040
If we can't sleep at night,

88
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:55,720
then you'll accompany me
to watch the sea at night.

89
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:58,199
Isn't it wonderful?

90
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:02,920
We can't be in love for a lifetime
without considering the reality problems.

91
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:06,800
If there's no future,
then I'm just wasting your time.

92
00:06:33,639 --> 00:06:40,199
So you are going to break up with me, right?

93
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:47,759
Ling Weiyi, let's break up.

94
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:53,839
You deserve someone better.

95
00:06:53,839 --> 00:06:55,959
And to you, I am

96
00:06:58,199 --> 00:07:00,296
not the one.

97
00:07:00,851 --> 00:07:04,640
♫ As time goes by ♫

98
00:07:04,640 --> 00:07:08,128
♫ I start to realize ♫

99
00:07:08,128 --> 00:07:10,080
♫ How much I miss you ♫

100
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:14,720
♫ I remember it as if it was yesterday ♫

101
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:18,336
♫ We used to share many memories ♫

102
00:07:18,336 --> 00:07:21,856
♫ But I've already locked them away ♫

103
00:07:21,856 --> 00:07:24,224
♫ Placed in a corner ♫

104
00:07:24,224 --> 00:07:28,896
♫ They're waiting to be found again ♫

105
00:07:28,896 --> 00:07:33,184
♫ Those cherished quiet moments ♫

106
00:07:33,184 --> 00:07:36,672
♫ Are hidden in the dark ♫

107
00:07:36,672 --> 00:07:43,328
♫ Light them up again and again,
and never let go ♫

108
00:07:43,328 --> 00:07:47,424
♫ The silent, everlasting promise ♫

109
00:07:47,424 --> 00:07:52,840
♫ Are secretly hidden within my heart ♫

110
00:07:56,480 --> 00:08:00,800
I remember we once watched a drama, Endless…

111
00:08:01,319 --> 00:08:04,959
What are you doing? Do you want
me to find someone else?

112
00:08:05,279 --> 00:08:07,759
That drama was a tragedy, wasn't it?

113
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:10,000
But I believe

114
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:12,240
we will definitely not end up like that.

115
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:15,000
You will be alright and so will I.

116
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:17,959
We will always be together,

117
00:08:17,959 --> 00:08:20,160
never apart.

118
00:08:34,759 --> 00:08:37,440
Why did you only run for half an hour today?

119
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:40,840
I had already run for an hour before you came.

120
00:08:44,399 --> 00:08:46,360
I thought

121
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:50,519
to exhaust my body, then I won't feel that bad.

122
00:08:50,879 --> 00:08:55,200
But I found the more tired I get,
the more I want to rely on someone.

123
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:01,000
Come on.

124
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:05,160
Lean on me.

125
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:08,720
I'm glad you are here.

126
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:13,919
But today, you…

127
00:09:13,919 --> 00:09:17,519
You have to find a new client
because of that scumbag named Fu.

128
00:09:17,519 --> 00:09:20,320
Isn't staying here with me
holding you back from your time?

129
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:22,759
My best friend just had a breakup.

130
00:09:22,759 --> 00:09:24,320
Why would I still work?

131
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:25,919
Work is not important now.

132
00:09:25,919 --> 00:09:28,639
Even if I had a client worth one billion
come to me right now,

133
00:09:28,639 --> 00:09:30,559
I wouldn't go to work.

134
00:09:30,559 --> 00:09:33,279
My only work today is to be with you.

135
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:35,639
A client worth one billion!

136
00:09:35,639 --> 00:09:37,919
Then you have to go.

137
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:41,600
What if your best friend
has a breakup every two months,

138
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:44,759
then you might miss the chance
to be the richest person in the world?

139
00:09:44,799 --> 00:09:47,159
Can you not jinx it, please?

140
00:09:47,159 --> 00:09:49,360
This breakup will be your last one.

141
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:53,080
The next person you meet
will surely like you very much,

142
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:56,759
treat you well
and want to stay with you for life.

143
00:09:57,720 --> 00:10:03,000
This time, just consider it a regret.

144
00:10:03,399 --> 00:10:07,679
Everyone has regrets in life.

145
00:10:07,679 --> 00:10:11,879
It's not fun to have no regrets, right?

146
00:10:18,919 --> 00:10:20,968
I'll get the phone.

147
00:10:24,639 --> 00:10:26,399
Tu, your friend, Mr. Yu,

148
00:10:26,399 --> 00:10:28,360
